-- Grainger posts higher quarterly earnings
-- 
-- Tue Jul 15, 2008 8:41am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/15/us-wwgrainger-results-idUSWNAB069020080715

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Industrial supplier W.W. Grainger Inc ( GWW.N ) posted higher quarterly earnings on Tuesday and reiterated its 2008 outlook, citing market share gains that fueled sales growth. 

 Net income in the second quarter rose 8 percent to $113 million, or $1.43 per share, from $105 million, or $1.21 per share, a year earlier. Excluding the effect of a provision for a legal reserve, earnings per share were $1.48. Analysts had predicted earnings of $1.46 per share, according to Reuters Estimates. Sales at the company, which sells such items as lighting, motors and janitorial supplies needed by contractors and facility managers to run their buildings, rose 10 percent to $1.8 billion, topping analyst estimates of $1.73 billion. In the United States, sales increased 9 percent, with the strongest growth coming from government and large national account customers. The company affirmed its 2008 guidance of earnings in the range of $5.80 per share to $6.10 per share. Analysts had forecast 2008 earnings per share of $5.89, according to Reuters Estimates. (Reporting by  Helen Chernikoff , editing by Gerald E. McCormick and Dave Zimmerman)